1. Open android studio
2. Select Configure
3. Select Settings
4. Select Version Control
5. Select Git
6. Enter C:\Temp\GitPortable\App\Git\cmd\git.exe into the 'Path to Git executable' field
7. Press test. If it's not successful search c drive for git.exe and use the path to that instead
8. Check out project from version control
9. Choose Git
10. Enter https://github.com/aidden93/KIT305_Assignment2.git as the repository URL
11. Choose the directory you want the project to be stored in
12. Press Clone

This should be all you need to get set up.
Make sure to perform a pull request every time you open the project to make sure you have the latest version of the files.
